jobs_results.title: Infrastructure Cloud Engineer (renewable one-year contract)
jobs_results.description:
A great Infrastructure Cloud Engineer (renewable one-year contract) job opportunity has become available at a multinational company.

About the Infrastructure Cloud Engineer (renewable one-year contract) Role:
You will be responsible for planning, designing and deployment of cloud workloads for Azure and AWS.

Key Responsibilities:
• Operations and incident management support for workload running on cloud
• Work with the project team, stakeholders and vendors to ensure cloud deployment is performed as per requirements
• Evaluate and suggest the most optimised method and cloud SKU
• Work with various teams to evaluate the suitability and feasibility of application deployment to cloud
• Keep track of cloud expenses in terms of commitment to various stakeholders
• Generate various reports related to cloud footprint and present to management
• Perform periodic reviews and suggest various improvements possible to the existing cloud deployment
• Plan, design and deploy cloud workloads for... Azure and AWS

To succeed in this Infrastructure Cloud Engineer (renewable one-year contract) role, you must have experience in Azure and AWS.

Key Requirements:
• Trained and certified in cloud:
• Microsoft Azure/AWS/Google environments and operations
• Cloud systems configuration management
• Hands-on experience in designing, creating and supporting Azure/AWS environment for a large enterprise
• Hands-on experience in setting up and on boarding Azure/AWS environment for a large enterprise
• Experience in troubleshooting common issues related to Azure/AWS
• Knowledge and experience in various Azure/AWS security features
• Strong batch and/or PowerShell scripting on Windows
• Monitoring and management tools on Azure/AWS
• Expertise in one or more of the following technical domains: Windows, Linux, Database, Storage, Networks, Scripting, Security
• Ability to learn and adapt to new frameworks/technologies and quickly integrate with them for automation service delivery
• Ability to find effective workarounds to product limitations/constraints
• Knowledge experience with DevOps/Automation tools is a plus

This company offers great opportunities to work with new technologies and has a leading market position.

If you are willing to join a multinational company, this Infrastructure Cloud Engineer (renewable one-year contract) role would be a great opportunity for you.

Apply today or contact me to discuss this role.

Do note that we will only be in touch if your application is shortlisted.

Robert Walters (Singapore) Pte Ltd

jobs_results.title: Software Engineering (Blockchain) - Associate
jobs_results.description:
As a member of our Software Engineering Group, we look first and foremost for people who are passionate around solving business problems through innovation and engineering practices. You'll be required to apply your depth of knowledge and expertise to all aspects of the software development lifecycle, as well as partner continuously with your many stakeholders on a daily basis to stay focused on common goals. We embrace a culture of experimentation and constantly strive for improvement and learning. You'll work in a collaborative, trusting, thought-provoking environment-one that encourages diversity of thought and creative solutions that are in the best interests of our customers globally.

This role is a software engineering role to develop applications that are based on Distributed Ledger Technology and encompasses both on-chain and off-chain component. This is a strategic initiative to leverage leading edge technologies to create new business capabilities and enable new business... models to gain competitive advantage. Apart from project delivery, a significant part of the role will be to evaluate and apply new technologies onto a broad spectrum of payment use cases through pilots and proof-of-concepts.

This role requires a wide variety of strengths and capabilities, including:
• BS/BA degree or equivalent experience
• Expertise in application, data and data architecture disciplines
• Proficiency in Java programming language and Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment
• Knowledge of industry-wide technology trends and best practices
• Ability to work in large, collaborative teams across geographical boundaries to achieve organizational goals
• Passionate about building an innovative culture
• At least 6 years of relevant technical experience in a software development role
• Strong analytical capabilities in troubleshooting testing and production defects to accelerate workaround and/or recovery and reduce downtime impact
• Prior working experience in the financial industry preferred, especially relating to high volume mission critical transactional systems
• Self-learner and adaptability to different technologies and programming languages
• Knowledge of payment processing, cloud hosting and blockchain technology are advantageous
• Experience in running complex in-house development projects with multiple interconnecting systems and interdependencies
• Good communication skills with ability to articulate implications of technology solutions to business stakeholders

J.P. Morgan is a global leader in financial services, providing strategic advice and products to the world's most prominent corporations, governments, wealthy individuals and institutional investors. Our first-class business in a first-class way approach to serving clients drives everything we do. We strive to build trusted, long-term partnerships to help our clients achieve their business objectives.

We recognize that our people are our strength and the diverse talents they bring to our global workforce are directly linked to our success. We are an equal opportunity employer and place a high value on diversity and inclusion at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of any protected attribute, including race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital or veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. In accordance with applicable law, we make reasonable accommodations for applicants' and employees' religious practices and beliefs, as well as any mental health or physical disability needs

jobs_results.title: Senior Software Engineer (Full Stack Developer – Java, .Net)
jobs_results.description:
We are looking for a highly skilled application programmer who is comfortable with both front and back end programming. Full Stack Developers are responsible for designing the application architecture, exploring best fit technology, developing the front end and back end components, and ensuring the applications performance, among other duties.
Full Stack Developers will be required to see out a project from conception to final product, as a sole contributor, or part of a developer team, that requiring good organizational skills and attention to detail. This role will also be responsible for the integration with different application frameworks and platforms within the organization’s Industry 4.0 digital solution ecosystem, as well as supporting exploration of new technology and innovation solution.

Roles and Responsibilities
(Essential roles, responsibilities an d activities a candidate can expect to assume in this
position)

• Works with application development team, business unit... process experts, and outsource technology partner to design and develop software applications.
• Evaluate and implement best fit frameworks and integrated development environment required to provide required development infrastructure
• Provide expertise to identify and translate system requirements into software design artefacts.
• Creates architecture designs (at conceptual and logical level) of large and complex systems in the enterprise with the aim to make the systems sustainable and future-proof after they have been realized
• Ensure the efficiency, security, and support of the organization's goals in the solution.
• Create methods for compliance architecture, such as data storage, metadata management, and change control.
• Synchronize IT systems in development plan with business needs
• Develop well designed, efficient, testable and high-quality code
• Develop front end application architecture - UI.
• Develop back end applications.
• Setting up apps servers and databases for functionality.
• Ensure applications performance (responsiveness) and friendliness - UX.
• Seeing through a project from conception to finished product.
• Design and develop APIs.

Minimum years of experience in role:
• experience in full software development lifecycle
• Extensive practical Enterprise Architecture experience, certified with a recognised EA framework, e.g. TOGAF
• Experience within Solution Design & Architecture
• Experience with Software Development Project Management
• Experience on Secure Software Development, secure code quality control, and application and system integration vulnerability assessment.
• Experience with Application Development and Software Assurance in a highly regulated industry
• Robust knowledge within Security Architecture
• Experience working within mobile, cloud and infrastructure solutions environments
• Proficiency with server side languages such as .Net, Node JS, Java, PHP, Python, etc.
• Proficiency with database technology such as Ms SQL, Oracle, MySQL and MongoDB.
• Proficiency with fundamental front end languages such as HTML, CSS and JavaScript (e.g Angular JS, React and Amber).
• Experience with mobile apps development
• Experience with Cloud services and cloud API services (Google Cloud, Azure, Amazon)
• Strong communication and interpersonal skills.
• Great individual performer as well as contributor in a team
• Good problem solving skills.

Preferred Skills (if any):
• Demonstrated Excellent level of analytical ability, communication and interpersonal skills required to build relationships with team members to solve problems and resolve issues.
• Experiences in full software development lifecycle
• Extensive practical Enterprise Architecture experience, certified with a recognised EA framework, e.g. TOGAF
• Experience within Solution Design & Architecture
